{
  "texts": [
    "These effects, along with the analysis of errors for SimVerb3500, are displayed in Fig. 3.",
    "Qualitative inspection revealed that some of the highest divergences were for word pairs that formed semantic complements in some way, e.g., \"wife/ husband\", \"south/north\", and \"groom/bride\".",
    "SimVerb3500.",
    "The SimVerb3500 dataset (Gerz et al., 2016) is annotated for the type of relation between the verbs in question: synonyms, co-hyponyms, hyper/hyponyms, antonyms, or none.",
    "GPT-4 achieved high correlations overall, but performance was considerably weaker for antonyms (see Fig. 3)."
  ]
}